Heres my understanding of what happens when an X application (like xterm)
needs to display text; It consults the system's font configuration...
Modern X11 systems typically rely on Fontconfig (a lib for managing fonts)
Fontconfig looks for fonts based on the user's preferences and available
fonts on the system, and it is likely configured to use Xft by default.
Xft, in turn, leverages the FreeType library for its core font rendering.
